INSTALLATION:

1) Move Makefile.all to Makefile.
2) Type 'make' should be enough to build libmalloc.a and malloc_debug program
3) typing 'make test' should build the malloc_test program
4) Examine the malloc.info file.  Is is a gnu-info file having the
	user-documentation for the malloc subsystem.
	It is also suitable for reading as text.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

- I am using gnu-make and gcc which is ansi-prototype compatible.
- the system is definately dependant on a good ansi-c compiler like gcc.
- The file Manifest contains a list of each of the file and what it does
